This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'copper slag' in a residual material landfill (RMLF). Recommended use of this dataset: for wastes-residues that are low in organic carbon (< 5 w-%) and are not biologically or chemically reactive in water.  Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% copper slag. Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): H2O na; O 366790; H na; C na; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl na; Br na; F na; I na; Ag 40; As 630; Ba 2400; Cd 40; Co na; Cr 280; Cu 8070; Hg 20; Mn 400; Mo na; Ni 2110; Pb 710; Sb na; Se 70; Sn na; V na; Zn 6060; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 155000; Fe 379000; Ca 7130; Al 26700; K 31700; Mg 4850; Na 8000.  Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 61.4%. 
Geography:  This dataset represents a landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 16.743579766537 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1250.84108527132 mm/year, mean annual actual evaporation (EAT) of 460.58904958214 mm/year, and net infiltration of 790.3 mm/year. The leachate percolating through the residual material landfill has an average residence time of 4.43 years.
Reference for climatic parameters:
UN data, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&d=ENV&f=variableID%3a6;
World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2;
Technology:  Residual material landfill for polluted, inorganic waste (VVEA Type C). With base seal and leachate collection system. Ultimate average landfill height is 10 meters. Operation phase duration is 30 years. Recultivation after closure. No additional solidification with cement requested. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase in the residual material landfill is estimated to be reached after 60 000 years.

The process represents the treatment of landfarming of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Sewage sludge with 97% water is generated during wastewater treatement (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of 'waste aluminium' . Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for 'waste aluminium'. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%.
Geography:  The site has mean annual temperature (MAT) of 9.5 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1483.00559816076 mm/year, mean annual actual evaporation (EAT) of 528.63778611689 mm/year. Climate will influence the local fate emissions based on the elemental composition of the sludge as well as water evaporation to air (= consumptive water use).
